			h1 Introduction
			p Barebones is a boilerplate to help you build your own UI framework. It is not a fully-fledged UI kit or library (Bootstrap, Foundation etc), but a set of tools common to all projects put together in a convenient package to kickstart your next project: 

			ul.bullet-list
				li a grid system 
				li commonly used mixins
				li reponsive helpers

			p Barebones is design-agnostic and fully customisable, so you can spend less time overwriting and more time creating.

			p To provide an example, this is the login modal on Airbnb, recreated using the various classes this is the sort of thing you can very quickly create with Barebones.



