		section(id="prerequisites")
			h2 Prerequisites
			p Barebones requires SASS v3.3 or later to compile <span class="inline-code">.scss</span> files into <span class="inline-code">.css</span>. Instructions can be found <a href="http://sass-lang.com/install" target="_blank" class="link">here</a>.

			p Additionally, vendor prefixing mixins are not used or included as you can use the <a href="https://github.com/postcss/autoprefixer" target="_blank" class="link">autoprefixer plugin</a> to do this.


		section(id="installation")

			h2 Get started

			h3 1. Install the package
			p Barebones is available as either a Bower or NPM package.
			.example.margin-bottom-8
				pre.example-code
					code.language-bash.
						bower install barebones-sass --save
			.example
				pre.example-code
					code.language-bash.
						npm install barebones-sass --save-dev

			p If you want to skip package control and copy the SASS files directly, you can do that too – simply download the latest release from <a href="https://github.com/sebpowell/barebones-sass" class="link">GitHub</a> and integrate the source files directly. 


			h3 2. Create a settings file

			p In your project folder, create a <span class="inline-code">_settings.scss</span> file (or whatever you want to call it) with the following values. Each setting is covered in the <a href="#" class="link">following section</a>.
			pre.example-code
				code.language-scss.
					$bb-border-radius-scale: 5;

					$bb-breakpoints: ();

					$bb-colors: ();

					$bb-letter-spacing: ();

					$bb-line-heights: ();

					$bb-global-delimiter: "-";

					$bb-helpers: ();

					$bb-hover-class-name: "hover";

					$bb-max-width-scale: 14;

					$bb-responsive: true;

					$bb-shadows: ();

					$bb-spacing-scale: 10;

					$bb-spacing-base: 4px;

					$bb-spacing-sides: ();

					$bb-text-sizes: ();


			p Barebones also allows you to specify your own naming convention. For each generated class, you can decide how that class will be outputted. Here's an example: 


			pre.example-code
				code.language-scss.
					$bb-align-items: (
						"modifiers": (
							"flex-start": "items-flex-start",
							"flex-end": "items-flex-end",
							"center": "items-center"
						)
					);

					// This is used by the align-items helper generator to create classes for the flex align-items property. 
					// By default, this will look like this: 

					.align-items-flex-start {}
					.align-items-flex-start {}
					.align-items-flex-start {}

					// You can make this less verbose by changing the names: 

					$bb-align-items: (
						"modifiers": (
							"flex-start": "items-fs",
							"flex-end": "items-fe",
							"center": "items-c"
						)
					);

					// Will output: 

					.items-fs {}
					.items-fe {}
					.items-c {}

			h3 3. Create your main SCSS file
			p he final step is to import all these files into your main files that will be compiled into actual CSS. When you're done, it should look something like this:

			.example
				pre.example-code
					code.language-scss.
						// Always import the settings file first
						@import _settings.scss;

						// Always import the settings file first
						@import bower-components/barebones-sass/dist/_base.scss;

